00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.000
[Terminal — ollama list — gemma4:e4b and gemma4:e2b installed]

00:00:04.000 --> 00:00:07.000
[Title — HealthPulse Edge · Quality intelligence for the smallest hospitals in America]

00:00:07.000 --> 00:00:15.000
1,350 hospitals carry Mayo Clinic's federal reporting obligations. No IT team. No analytics staff. No internet right now.

00:00:15.000 --> 00:00:28.000
Marlene runs quality at Sage Mesa Critical Access Hospital. Her overnight question — top three care gaps — was answered while the hospital slept. Gemma 4 ranked them. Recommendation: heart failure readmissions, excess ratio one-point-two-one.

00:00:28.000 --> 00:00:39.000
Last night's batch also processed patient surveys. Gemma 4 vision read this one on-device — initials, visit date, free-text. The image never left the building.

00:00:39.000 --> 00:00:42.000
[Title — The policy gate · Sovereignty Mode · redaction · differential privacy · sign]

00:00:42.000 --> 00:00:51.000
Quarter-end. CMS reporting is due. Watch what the policy does. Sovereignty Mode off — the envelope sails through.

00:00:51.000 --> 00:01:00.000
Sovereignty Mode on — same submit, blocked. CMS needs the tribal council co-signature key. She pastes it.

00:01:00.000 --> 00:01:09.000
The redaction sub-agent strips two hundred five PHI fields. Differential privacy on five aggregates. Epsilon five spent.

00:01:09.000 --> 00:01:13.000
Here it is on a single record — every PHI substring becomes a token before anything leaves the building.

00:01:13.000 --> 00:01:16.000
[Title — Cryptographic audit trail · Every action logged to a SHA-256 chain the hospital cannot forge]

00:01:16.000 --> 00:01:23.000
Every tool call, every redaction, every egress — appended to a SHA-256 chain. Click verify. Six entries confirmed.

00:01:23.000 --> 00:01:26.000
[Title — Same product, in your browser · Gemma 4 runs in WebGPU · no server · works offline]

00:01:26.000 --> 00:01:35.000
The whole product also runs in your browser. WebGPU loads Gemma 4 once — then offline. Same tools, same ledger, same proof.

00:01:35.000 --> 00:01:39.770
